  "$schema": "https://aka.ms/codetour-schema",
  "title": "2 â€” Backend Walkthrough",
  "steps": [
    {
      "file": "src/BdoWeather.Api/Program.cs",
      "line": 17,
      "description": "### Config binding\n`WeatherApiOptions` is bound from `appsettings.json`. The `ApiKey` must be supplied via user secrets (local dev) or an environment variable (CI/production) â€” it is validated on start-up via `[Required]` + `ValidateOnStart()`."
    },
    {
      "file": "src/BdoWeather.Api/Infrastructure/WeatherApiOptions.cs",
      "line": 1,
      "description": "### Options record\nImmutable config record. `UseMock` lets the entire OWM integration be bypassed without any code change â€” just flip the flag in config."
    },
    {
      "file": "src/BdoWeather.Api/Infrastructure/IWeatherApiClient.cs",
      "line": 1,
      "description": "### Testability boundary\nFeature handlers only depend on `IWeatherApiClient`, never on `WeatherApiClient` directly. This means NSubstitute can substitute the interface in tests without touching the network."
    },
    {
      "file": "src/BdoWeather.Api/Infrastructure/WeatherApiClient.cs",
      "line": 1,
      "description": "### OWM adapter\nMaps the raw OpenWeatherMap JSON response into a domain `WeatherResponse`. All HTTP status code handling (404 â†’ city not found, 429 â†’ rate limited) happens here, keeping feature handlers clean."
    },
    {
      "file": "src/BdoWeather.Api/Common/ResultTypes.cs",
      "line": 1,
      "description": "### Result<T>\nFeature handlers return `Result<T>` instead of throwing. `IsSuccess`, `IsFailure`, `Value`, and `Match<>` provide exhaustive handling. Exceptions are reserved for truly unrecoverable conditions."
    },
    {
      "file": "src/BdoWeather.Api/Common/ResultExtensions.cs",
      "line": 1,
      "description": "### HTTP mapping\n`ToHttpResult<T>` converts a `Result<T>` to the correct `IResult` â€” 200, 404, 429, or 500. The `ApiEnvelope` wrapper ensures all responses have a consistent `{ data, errors }` shape."
    },
    {
      "file": "src/BdoWeather.Api/Features/Weather/GetWeatherByCity.cs",
      "line": 1,
      "description": "### Weather feature handler\nCache-first: checks `IMemoryCache` before calling OWM. Only successful responses are cached (failures are not stored). TTL comes from `WeatherApiOptions.CacheTtlMinutes`."
    },
    {
      "file": "src/BdoWeather.Api/Features/DefaultLocation/SetDefaultLocation.cs",
      "line": 1,
      "description": "### Set default location\nValidates input with FluentValidation â†’ verifies the city exists via OWM â†’ removes any existing default â†’ saves new one. Always one row in the table. Cache is invalidated on success."
    },
    {
      "file": "src/BdoWeather.Api/Persistence/AppDbContext.cs",
      "line": 1,
      "description": "### EF Core context\n`ApplyConfigurationsFromAssembly` auto-discovers all `IEntityTypeConfiguration<T>` implementations. SQLite in development; the connection string is overridable via `ConnectionStrings:Default` in config."
    },
    {
      "file": "src/BdoWeather.Api/Common/GlobalExceptionHandler.cs",
      "line": 1,
      "description": "### Exception handler\nCatches anything that escapes feature handlers (should be rare). Logs the full exception, returns a 500 envelope â€” never exposes stack traces to the client."
    },
    {
      "file": "src/BdoWeather.Tests/Features/Weather/GetWeatherByCityTests.cs",
      "line": 1,
      "description": "### Weather tests (xUnit)\nFour tests: happy path, city not found, cache hit on second call, upstream error not cached. Uses NSubstitute for `IWeatherApiClient` and EF InMemory for the DB."
    },
    {
      "file": "src/BdoWeather.Tests/Features/DefaultLocation/SetDefaultLocationTests.cs",
      "line": 1,
      "description": "### Default location tests\nFour tests: valid set, empty city validation, city not found by OWM, second set replaces first (upsert semantics). xUnit + Shouldly + NSubstitute."
    }
  ]
}
